The paper deals with coding theory, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT). The use of matrices and their properties suggests that the paper may also belong to the subfields of data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The study of minimum distance and duals of codes is also relevant to the subfield of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the use of matrices and their properties may also be relevant to the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG).
